b'' b'i was posting to alt.locksmithing about the best methods for securing' b'a motorcycle. i got several responses referring to the cobra lock' b'(described below). has anyone come across a store carrying this lock' b'in the chicago area?' b'' b'any other feedback from someone who has used this?' b'' b'thanks for any info.,' b'' b'steve' b'' b'' b" incidentally, the best lock i've found for bikes is the cobra lock." b" it's a cable which is shrouded by an articulated, hardened steel sleeve." b' the lock itself is cylindrical and the locking pawl engages the joints' b' at the articulation points so the chain can be adjusted (like handcuffs).' b" you can't get any leverage on the lock to break it open and the cylinder" b" is well-protected. i wouldn't want to cut one of these without a torch" b' and/or a vice and heavy duty cutting wheel.' b'' b'' b'' b'---' b'steve bunis, sun microsystems ***dod #0795***\t93-st1100' b'itasca, il\t ***ama #682049***\t78-kz650' b'' 